    <div class="container" role="main" aria-live="polite">
        <h1>IT Resilience: Rural Supply Chain Disruption ðŸŒ²</h1>
        <p>A regional landslide has closed the only highway to <strong>North Creek Community Hospital</strong>. No medical deliveries will arrive for 5 days. Here is how IT shifts from "fixing computers" to "sustaining care."</p>

        <div id="step1" class="activity-section">
            <h2>Phase 1: Real-Time Resource Visibility</h2>
            <p>Without a proactive system, the hospital wouldn't know they are out of oxygen sensors until a nurse reaches for an empty box. IT enables visibility:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Inventory Interfacing:</strong> IT links the Warehouse Management System (WMS) directly to the EHR dashboard so doctors see "Low Stock" icons while writing orders.</li>
                <li><strong>Predictive Analytics:</strong> Using historical data, IT generates a report showing which supplies will run out first based on current patient acuity.</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="proactive-tip">
                <strong>Proactive Move:</strong> IT sets up automated "PAR level" alerts that text the Incident Command team the moment life-saving supplies drop below 20%.
            </div>
            <button onclick="showStep(2)">Step 2: Virtualizing Care</button>
        </div>

        <div id="step2" class="activity-section hidden">
            <h2>Phase 2: Stretching Physical Resources</h2>
            <p>When physical supplies are stuck, IT uses digital solutions to "extend" what is available:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Tele-Specialist Activation:</strong> Since onsite specialists can't travel to the hospital, IT spins up high-def video carts for remote neurology and cardiology consults.</li>
                <li><strong>Remote Patient Monitoring (RPM):</strong> IT configures tablets for stable patients to be monitored from home, freeing up limited on-site supplies and beds for emergencies.</li>
            </ul>
            <button onclick="showStep(3)">Step 3: Localized Redundancy</button>
        </div>

        <div id="step3" class="activity-section hidden">
            <h2>Phase 3: Preventing the "Second Crisis"</h2>
            <p>A supply crisis often leads to equipment failure. IT ensures the existing tech doesn't quit when it's needed most:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Biomedical Integration:</strong> IT uses network monitoring to track the "health" of ventilators and dialysis machines, ensuring preventive maintenance is done before a part breaks.</li>
                <li><strong>Offline EHR Mode:</strong> If the landslide also severed the fiber-optic internet line, IT activates "Downtime Computers" that contain local copies of patient records.</li>
            </ul>
            <button onclick="alert('Case Study Complete: Your proactive IT strategy saved North Creek from a total service shutdown.')">Complete Review</button>
        </div>
    </div>

    <script>
        function showStep(n) {
            document.querySelectorAll('.activity-section').forEach(s => s.classList.add('hidden'));
            document.getElementById('step' + n).classList.remove('hidden');
            window.scrollTo(0,0);
        }
    </script>
